         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
               <supplied reason="lost">with so-and-so</supplied> his wife from his own resources having constructed the south <supplied reason="lost">stoa</supplied> of the archive <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The association of c with the other fragments, originally made by Robert, appears very likely.  It is very probable that these blocks come from the same building as <ref type="inscription" n="1028" target="121006.xml"/> (=MAMA 498) (which was also reused in the construction of the West gate) and come from one of the buildings constructed by Jason Prabreus and his wife, Julia Paula.</p>
         </div>
